      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPLASH OF STEEL (6) was enormous first-up in the Magic Millions Maiden, coming from near the tail to get up for second over 1100m at the Gold Coast. Missed the jump and was never in contention last start at Warwick Farm. Needs 1400m now and the wide-open spaces of Scone are perfect. This looks his race. PAPPA BLUE (4) came from next to last after a poor start to be beaten under a length when resuming over 1200m at Canberra last time. Crying out for 1400m with that run under the belt. Draws the fence so needs to get away okay to take advantage. SCOOP THE POOL (5) is back from a 20-week spell. Competitive at the provincials last prep and a recent trial win suggests he is ready to recapture that form from the get-go. SHAKESPEARE'S GIRL (8) won a recent trial and appears set to make a solid return from a brief spell. Hard to see the other two runners making an impact.",
